Interesting.  This is happening because we explicitly disallow `None` in `type_caster_generic::load()` (the base type caster for user-declared types):
```C++
        if (src.is_none()) {
            value = nullptr;
            return true;
        }
```
which usually seems pretty reasonable, but does indeed cause this.

